275
00:24:30,950 --> 00:24:32,570
<i>If you...</i>

276
00:24:33,490 --> 00:24:36,180
end up finding Min Ho,

277
00:24:36,180 --> 00:24:40,800
I want you to hold his funeral for me.

278
00:24:47,390 --> 00:24:51,530
Next time I come to my senses,

279
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:54,810
if I get to hear that...

280
00:24:54,810 --> 00:24:57,730
Min Ho is resting somewhere sunny and

281
00:24:57,730 --> 00:25:01,170
has a great view of sunset like this,

282
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:04,190
I want...

283
00:25:06,070 --> 00:25:08,530
nothing more.

284
00:25:12,590 --> 00:25:15,890
Please make sure that happens.

285
00:25:17,780 --> 00:25:21,510
I'm sure Min Ho will finally tell us

286
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:25,430
what happened 15 years ago.

287
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:30,720
- But there's one thing that bothers me.
- Huh?

288
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:34,900
Jo Seong Wuk talked to someone
on the phone on the way here.

289
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:38,600
<i>He didn't hang up until he exhumed the body.</i>

290
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:43,460
As if he were asking for permission.

291
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:48,390
Another person connected
to Park Min Ho's death?

292
00:25:48,390 --> 00:25:49,870
Yes.

293
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:54,850
He hasn't yet shown himself to us.

294
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,830
Another perpetrator.

295
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:24,720
Gwang Jin.

296
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:28,370
Gosh. The successful Coach Jo Seong Wuk.

297
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:32,490
Hyung, long time no see.

298
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:34,190
H-Have you been well?

299
00:26:34,190 --> 00:26:36,380
You haven't aged at all.

300
00:26:36,380 --> 00:26:37,930
Sit.

301
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:40,480
Okay. It's biting.

302
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:42,120
All right.

303
00:27:02,610 --> 00:27:03,980
What?

304
00:27:03,980 --> 00:27:06,120
You didn't catch fish.

305
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:10,870
Dong Hyeon, you're playing this wrong.

306
00:27:10,870 --> 00:27:14,330
I told you to shake the bobber
after catching the fish.

307
00:27:15,120 --> 00:27:17,830
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

308
00:27:17,830 --> 00:27:22,150
Please forgive me just once. Please...

309
00:27:22,150 --> 00:27:23,750
Just once?

310
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,350
Okay.

311
00:27:27,350 --> 00:27:29,790
Let's do better this time.

312
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:32,690
Fighting.

313
00:27:32,690 --> 00:27:35,790
Please! Spare me!

314
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:42,440
Seong Wuk, come here.

315
00:27:48,770 --> 00:27:50,740
What's all this?

316
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:53,900
That the rules of the game you
set suddenly changed.

317
00:27:53,900 --> 00:27:55,590
You got a text from Min Ho.

318
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:59,710
And someone who knew all about this showed up.

319
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:03,440
Dong Hyeon has always been
bad at explaining things.

320
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:06,020
I have no idea what this all means.

321
00:28:06,020 --> 00:28:10,560
G-Gwang Jin, the bobber moved. The bobber.

322
00:28:13,270 --> 00:28:14,410
Don't worry.

323
00:28:14,410 --> 00:28:17,170
No, no. The bobber moved.

324
00:28:17,170 --> 00:28:20,160
That bastard is lying.

325
00:28:22,330 --> 00:28:24,670
Should I tell you a secret?

326
00:28:25,830 --> 00:28:31,140
There's no fish in here.

327
00:28:49,150 --> 00:28:52,700
Instead of Dong Hyeon, who's bad at explaining,

328
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:57,020
you should explain, so I can
understand, Seong Wuk.

329
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:04,340
Why did you dig up Min Ho?

330
00:29:10,490 --> 00:29:11,800
<i>According to the DNA test,</i>

331
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:15,650
