468
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:20,020
<i>My family thought I made a mistake and</i>

469
00:41:20,020 --> 00:41:22,280
<i>covered it up for me.</i>

470
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:27,570
<i>But my grandma figured out what happened.</i>

471
00:41:27,570 --> 00:41:29,500
That it wasn't a mistake.

472
00:41:29,500 --> 00:41:33,940
Geez. Isn't it so crazy when you think about it?

473
00:41:33,940 --> 00:41:36,350
How did Grandma figure it out?

474
00:41:37,220 --> 00:41:41,800
<i>So, she built this school urgently.</i>

475
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:45,850
To trap me here after I graduated
from elementary school.

476
00:41:45,850 --> 00:41:48,820
Sounds like the school resembles you.

477
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:52,380
It's filled with nothing but trash.

478
00:41:53,700 --> 00:41:56,690
My grandma was trash, not me.

479
00:41:56,690 --> 00:41:59,690
She shouldn't have done that
to her grandson as a grown-up.

480
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:02,880
But do you know what's crazier?

481
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:07,630
I found out about her plan.

482
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:13,960
You should've left the bygones be bygones.

483
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:18,070
Why are you digging things up now? Huh?

484
00:42:20,010 --> 00:42:22,600
Where's Park Min Ho's body right now?

485
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:25,730
Oh, right. That's why you came.

486
00:42:27,630 --> 00:42:30,150
Let's see.

487
00:42:30,150 --> 00:42:34,880
There's an item under the statue to your right.

488
00:42:41,330 --> 00:42:42,830
[The Grandmother and Her Grandson]

489
00:43:02,110 --> 00:43:04,400
What's this now?

490
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,560
