533
00:48:12,990 --> 00:48:19,420
Mr. Kim, you're on air on the dark web abroad.

534
00:48:25,830 --> 00:48:29,650
They're betting on you. Are they crazy?

535
00:48:52,100 --> 00:48:55,350
Look at his defense skills. Seriously.

536
00:49:02,740 --> 00:49:05,140
[Player]

537
00:49:05,140 --> 00:49:08,320
Go Eun, can you find out where
the broadcasting room is?

538
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,560
Broadcasting room?

539
00:49:09,560 --> 00:49:12,980
Cheon Gwang Jin sounded the school bell.

540
00:49:12,980 --> 00:49:14,870
I'll guide you there now.

541
00:49:26,490 --> 00:49:28,490
What an interesting bastard.

542
00:49:29,340 --> 00:49:31,670
- Connect the hallway.
- Got it.

543
00:49:37,630 --> 00:49:41,220
<i>The broadcasting room is the last room upstairs.</i>

544
00:49:45,710 --> 00:49:49,050
What? Why did it turn off? The next hallway.

545
00:49:54,440 --> 00:49:57,160
Shit. Can't you control properly, you bastard?

546
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:58,650
I didn't do that.

547
00:49:58,650 --> 00:50:00,380
Someone must be controlling it outside.

548
00:50:00,380 --> 00:50:02,450
- What?
- The direction keys are not working.

549
00:50:02,450 --> 00:50:05,080
Of course, they aren't.

550
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:07,890
Shit.

551
00:50:09,660 --> 00:50:10,770
Yup!

552
00:50:10,770 --> 00:50:13,820
Hey, people are leaving.
My money. Damn it. My money!

553
00:50:13,820 --> 00:50:15,040
It turned off again.

554
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:17,020
Damn it!

555
00:50:19,340 --> 00:50:21,460
You can't see anything, can you?

556
00:50:22,820 --> 00:50:26,170
Wow. What a funny situation.

557
00:50:28,200 --> 00:50:30,310
Why doesn't it work? Why?

558
00:50:30,310 --> 00:50:31,690
Restore it now.

559
00:50:31,690 --> 00:50:33,890
What do you mean, why?

560
00:50:38,970 --> 00:50:42,580
What are you guys doing?
Aren't you going to check?

561
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:54,390
[Round 3]

562
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:59,620
<i>Round 3. Fight.</i>

563
00:51:20,070 --> 00:51:23,710
You're surprisingly good at this game.

564
00:51:23,710 --> 00:51:26,910
Do you want to make a fortune with me?

565
00:51:40,390 --> 00:51:44,350
They think everyone on the screen is a player.

566
00:51:44,350 --> 00:51:47,890
It seems like everyone wants you dead.

567
00:51:47,890 --> 00:51:49,360
That must be a more lucrative option.

568
00:51:49,360 --> 00:51:51,650
It is to me.

569
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:55,390
Because you'll die here.

570
00:51:56,300 --> 00:51:59,530
Everyone is betting on you like crazy.

571
00:52:18,490 --> 00:52:21,230
[Staff of love]

572
00:52:21,230 --> 00:52:23,680
They still have something like this at school.

573
00:52:28,030 --> 00:52:30,000
The staff of love.

574
00:52:39,850 --> 00:52:41,370
Does it hurt?

575
00:52:43,100 --> 00:52:45,670
You should've...

576
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:49,570
listened to your teacher.

577
00:53:02,570 --> 00:53:06,700
Wow. You reached the last stage in the game.

578
00:53:31,910 --> 00:53:33,990
You're too slow.

579
00:54:17,110 --> 00:54:19,040
You're too slow, too.

580
00:54:32,870 --> 00:54:35,320
This is what connects us.

581
00:55:15,230 --> 00:55:18,800
You're here for Park Min Ho's body.

582
00:55:18,800 --> 00:55:20,890
I'll tell you where it is.

583
00:55:21,770 --> 00:55:23,930
Thank you, but no thanks.

584
00:55:23,930 --> 00:55:25,860
I already found it.

585
00:55:37,280 --> 00:55:39,810
We have Mr. Park Min Ho.

586
00:55:42,610 --> 00:55:46,100
How much did the old man pay you?

587
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:49,020
I'll...

588
00:55:49,950 --> 00:55:53,440
I'll pay you 10 times. Ten times more.

589
00:55:56,810 --> 00:55:58,920
No good?

590
00:55:58,920 --> 00:56:00,970
T-Twenty times more?

591
00:56:03,270 --> 00:56:05,810
I refuse again.

592
00:56:05,810 --> 00:56:08,560
You'll have to die, then.

593
00:56:24,130 --> 00:56:27,130
I eyeballed it, but it fits perfectly.

594
00:56:32,950 --> 00:56:35,260
Okay.

595
00:56:35,260 --> 00:56:37,470
It hurts.

596
00:56:37,470 --> 00:56:40,830
I think all my bones are broken.

597
00:56:43,640 --> 00:56:45,210
You know what?

598
00:56:45,210 --> 00:56:47,710
Falling from the third floor is

599
00:56:47,710 --> 00:56:51,960
similar to getting hit by a car
driving 60 km per hour.

600
00:56:53,860 --> 00:56:56,000
It hurts.

601
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:01,230
I-I need to see a doctor.

602
00:57:02,220 --> 00:57:05,450
Park Min Ho and his father, Park Dong Su,

603
00:57:05,450 --> 00:57:08,390
whom you hit with a car.
I'm sure they felt the same.

604
00:57:12,070 --> 00:57:14,270
What did you do then?

605
00:57:15,940 --> 00:57:18,400
Did you just watch them?

606
00:57:22,040 --> 00:57:24,060
Laughing like this?

607
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:31,290
Spare me.

608
00:57:34,060 --> 00:57:37,060
Spare me.

609
00:57:37,060 --> 00:57:40,730
I won't do it again...

610
00:57:42,990 --> 00:57:46,370
Why? Are you afraid?

611
00:57:46,370 --> 00:57:49,070
That you'd disappear without a trace?

612
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:54,830
You understand how I feel.

613
00:57:54,830 --> 00:57:58,030
I know you aren't a bad person.

614
00:58:09,930 --> 00:58:12,560
You are.

615
00:58:25,410 --> 00:58:27,960
Kill me now, then.

616
00:58:29,550 --> 00:58:32,650
You'll kill me, anyway.

617
00:58:45,010 --> 00:58:48,610
This is the amount of time
Park Min Ho's father had each day.

618
00:58:48,610 --> 00:58:50,680
<i>Three minutes.</i>

619
00:58:50,680 --> 00:58:55,210
<i>The only time he had in his life
to remember his son.</i>

620
00:59:00,390 --> 00:59:04,000
Think carefully until all the sand falls.

621
00:59:04,000 --> 00:59:09,160
If there's a single person
who'd truly remember you.

622
00:59:30,070 --> 00:59:31,570
Is there one?

623
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:44,700
Yes!

624
00:59:45,470 --> 00:59:47,430
You!

625
00:59:48,850 --> 00:59:53,270
You have to remember!

626
01:00:05,730 --> 01:00:09,560
[The frequency of being alert
has been reducing...]

627
01:00:11,900 --> 01:00:14,140
<i>Hey!</i>

628
01:00:15,070 --> 01:00:19,920
You have to remember!

629
01:00:48,890 --> 01:00:51,210
Min Ho!

630
01:00:51,210 --> 01:00:53,280
Min Ho!

631
01:00:53,280 --> 01:00:54,870
Dad, hurry!

632
01:00:54,870 --> 01:00:57,450
The sun just started setting!

633
01:00:59,820 --> 01:01:03,600
I didn't think you'd be here on the way up here.

634
01:01:03,600 --> 01:01:07,100
Why wouldn't I be here? I promised you.

635
01:01:07,100 --> 01:01:11,610
We promised to come back here.

636
01:01:11,610 --> 01:01:14,330
The sky is so pretty today, too.

637
01:01:15,890 --> 01:01:18,830
I knew you'd find me, Dad.

638
01:01:21,150 --> 01:01:24,490
I'm sorry. I took too long, didn't I?

639
01:01:24,490 --> 01:01:26,480
No.

640
01:01:29,500 --> 01:01:34,880
Dad, you went through so much looking for me.

641
01:01:34,880 --> 01:01:37,240
You really did.

642
01:01:41,050 --> 01:01:46,150
Dad, I'll go ahead and wait for you there.

643
01:01:46,150 --> 01:01:48,250
You take your time.

644
01:01:48,250 --> 01:01:50,690
Take all the time you need to come.

645
01:01:50,690 --> 01:01:52,280
Okay?

646
01:01:54,210 --> 01:01:56,350
Don't worry about me.

647
01:01:56,350 --> 01:01:58,080
Min Ho...

648
01:02:01,520 --> 01:02:03,230
Thank you.

649
01:02:55,670 --> 01:02:59,260
<i>Give me a call, Dong Su.</i>

650
01:03:07,260 --> 01:03:09,040
Dong Su,

651
01:03:10,420 --> 01:03:14,750
I've been waiting for this phone to ring.

652
01:03:15,960 --> 01:03:19,750
You should send off Min Ho...

653
01:03:19,750 --> 01:03:22,410
your son for the last time.

654
01:03:28,570 --> 01:03:30,670
Thank you.

655
01:03:30,670 --> 01:03:32,300
Thank you so much.

656
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:40,010
<i>♫ I'm being pushed by the wind ♫</i>

657
01:03:40,010 --> 01:03:43,590
<i>♫ The sun is getting further away ♫</i>

658
01:03:43,590 --> 01:03:48,190
[Park Min Ho]

659
01:03:48,190 --> 01:03:56,320
<i>♫ Before the darkness comes ♫</i>

660
01:03:56,320 --> 01:04:01,950
<i>♫ I would like to see you once more ♫</i>

661
01:04:04,060 --> 01:04:11,110
<i>♫ Even somewhere far away ♫</i>

662
01:04:12,470 --> 01:04:18,890
<i>♫ Even at this remote place ♫</i>

663
01:04:21,980 --> 01:04:23,600
Min Ho...

664
01:04:25,850 --> 01:04:27,860
The sky is beautiful.

665
01:04:28,710 --> 01:04:31,230
It's just the way you like it.

666
01:04:32,840 --> 01:04:34,520
Look over there.

667
01:04:35,790 --> 01:04:39,980
You're right. It's so pretty today, too.

668
01:04:44,730 --> 01:04:49,600
<i>♫ I should take you with me ♫</i>

669
01:04:49,600 --> 01:05:03,900
<i>♫ Until you and I disappear into that sunset ♫</i>

670
01:05:05,600 --> 01:05:20,720
<i>♫ Until that wind erases me away ♫</i>

671
01:05:20,720 --> 01:05:25,170
<i>♫ I should wait for you ♫</i>

672
01:05:28,770 --> 01:05:33,820
<i>♫ I should embrace you ♫</i>

673
01:05:36,120 --> 01:05:42,920
<i>♫ The red sunset ♫</i>

674
01:05:43,990 --> 01:05:50,780
<i>♫ The cooling sunlight ♫</i>

675
01:05:52,520 --> 01:05:58,470
<i>♫ So I won't be afraid ♫</i>

676
01:05:58,470 --> 01:06:04,990
<i>♫ What am I supposed to do? ♫</i>

677
01:06:08,780 --> 01:06:13,420
<i>♫ I should wait for you ♫</i>

678
01:06:16,590 --> 01:06:21,530
<i>♫ I should stay with you ♫</i>

679
01:06:21,530 --> 01:06:28,090
<i>♫ While I'm absorbed in the sunset ♫</i>

680
01:06:28,090 --> 01:06:35,460
<i>♫ Until I get submerged into darkness ♫</i>

681
01:06:37,460 --> 01:06:43,930
<i>♫ Until that wind pushes me away ♫</i>

682
01:06:43,930 --> 01:06:53,170
<i>♫ Until I'm all washed away ♫</i>

683
01:06:53,170 --> 01:06:57,120
<i>♫ I should wait for you ♫</i>

684
01:06:58,790 --> 01:07:06,170
<i>♫ How could I leave you behind? ♫</i>

685
01:07:10,450 --> 01:07:14,090
<i>My dream was to become an idol.</i>

686
01:07:14,090 --> 01:07:18,050
<i>I'm going all-in on you
by betting everything I have.</i>

687
01:07:18,050 --> 01:07:19,380
<i>Where are we going?</i>

688
01:07:19,380 --> 01:07:22,560
<i>When I woke up, I was at a strange place.</i>

689
01:07:22,560 --> 01:07:25,620
<i>What am I supposed to do?</i>

690
01:07:25,620 --> 01:07:27,540
<i>If you can't debut now, you'll be disbanded.</i>

691
01:07:27,540 --> 01:07:29,760
<i>I don't know anything.</i>

692
01:07:29,760 --> 01:07:32,540
<i>Just think about how desperate you were.</i>

693
01:07:32,540 --> 01:07:35,970
<i>If the management company
threatened our client...</i>

694
01:07:35,970 --> 01:07:37,790
<i>You need to take a few beatings today.</i>

695
01:07:37,790 --> 01:07:40,042
<i>I think we need an insider.</i>

696
01:07:40,042 --> 01:07:42,373
<i>Let's change the manager.</i>
